{{For|the commune|Crivăţ, Călăraşi}}
{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''''Crivăț''''' ({{IPA-ro|ˈkrivət͡s}}) is a north-easterly wind in [[Moldavia]], [[Dobruja]], and the [[Bărăgan Plain]] parts of [[Romania]]. In the winter, it blows at speeds of up to 30–35&nbsp;m/s (108–126&nbsp;km/h, 67-78&nbsp;mph), creating [[blizzard]] conditions.

