{{for|the nineteenth century province|Mérida Province (Gran Colombia)}}
{{unreferenced|date=July 2010}}
[[File:Provincia de Mérida 1622-1676.PNG|thumb|right|Province of Mérida]]
'''Mérida Province''' was a [[province]] of the [[Spanish Empire]] in the 17th century (1622–1676), with [[Mérida, Mérida|Mérida]] as its capital. It was part of the [[New Kingdom of Granada]], and was formed initially in 1607 with a merger with the [[La Grita Province]], forming an administrative unit below province status (''Corregimiento de Mérida y La Grita''), which it attained in 1622. In 1676 it merged with [[Maracaibo]] to form what became known as [[Maracaibo Province (Spanish Empire)|Maracaibo Province]].

